st 400 years. Analyses throughout rethink the significance of theatre, dance, opera, circus, and other performance genres and events. This landmark collection challenges readers to reconsider Canadian theatre and performance history. Contributors: Clarence S. Bayne, Kym Bird, Justin A. Blum, Amy Bowring, Jill Carter, Jenn Cole, Cynthia Cooper, Heather Davis-Fisch, Moira J. Day, Ray Ellenwood, Alan Filewod, Howard Fink, Liza Giffen, J. Paul Halferty, James Hoffman, Erin Hurley, John D. Jackson, Stephen Johnson, Sasha Kovacs, Sylvain Lavoie, Louis Patrick Leroux, Allana C. Lindgren, Denyse Lynde, Erin Joelle McCurdy, Wing Chung Ng, Glen F. Nichols, M. Cody Poulton, VK Preston, Daniel J. Ruppel, Jordan Stanger-Ross, Paul J. Stoesser, Christl Verduyn, Anthony J. Vickery, Anton Wagner  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCanadian dramaxHistory and criticismvSources. 0aCanadian drama. 0aPerforming artszCanadaxHistoryvSources. 0aPerforming arts. 0aTheaterzCanadaxHistoryvSources. 0aTheater. 4aArt & Performance / Performing Arts. 4aArt & Performance. 4aLiterary Studies / Literary Criticism. 4aLiterary Studies. 7aDRAMA / Canadian.2bisacsh  atheatre drama plays scripts dance opera radio circus performance history historiography Canada Indigenous colonization Canadian Studies Cultural Studies anthology Pre-Confederation archive archival primary document choreography festivals race gender.1 aBayne, Clarence S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBird, Kym, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlum, Justin A ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBowring, Amy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarter, Jill, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCock